<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc9d9ace7-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s422c"><num value="422c">§ 422c.</num><heading> Proposals; submission; payment for cost of examination</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any organization desiring to avail itself of the benefits provided in this subchapter shall submit a proposal therefor to the Secretary in such form and manner as he shall prescribe. Each such proposal shall be accompanied by a payment of $5,000 to defray, in part, the cost of examining the proposal.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc9d9ace8-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-08-06/ch972/s3">Aug. 6, 1956, ch. 972, § 3</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70/1044">70 Stat. 1044</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/99/546/tIII/s303">Pub. L. 99–546, title III, § 303</ref>, <date date="1986-10-27">Oct. 27, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/3053">100 Stat. 3053</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc9d9ace9-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idc9d9acea-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idc9d9aceb-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1986—<ref href="/us/pl/99/546">Pub. L. 99–546</ref> substituted “$5,000” for “$1,000”.</p>
</note>
